1. Basic Battery Parameters: The battery type is Lithium Iron Phosphate (LiFePO₄, LFP), manufactured by A123 Systems, model APR18650M1A; nominal capacity is 1.1 Ah, and nominal voltage is 3.3 V.

2. Charging Procedure: A 4-stage constant current (CC) fast charge is applied up to 80% SOC. The first 3 stages each charge by 20% SOC (corresponding to the 0%-20%, 20%-40%, and 40%-60% intervals). The charging rate for the fourth stage must be set so that the total fast charging time is exactly 10 minutes. Afterwards, a constant current-constant voltage (CC-CV) mode is used to fully charge the battery.

3. Data Scope: The complete "cycle-to-failure" data of the final batch of 45 batteries was used. Based on different charging strategies, they are divided into 9 groups (5 batteries per group), with each group corresponding to a different combination of 4-stage charging rates.

The 9 .mat files correspond respectively to the 9 groups of batteries with different charging strategies, and each file contains five sets of experiments conducted on the same type of battery.

Group 1: Charging protocol (rates for 0-20%-40%-60%-80% stages): 3.6-6-5.6-4.755; Corresponding channels: 11, 12, 27, 29, 38
Group 2: Charging protocol: 4.4-5.6-5.2-4.252; Corresponding channels: 8, 15, 18, 32, 48
Group 3: Charging protocol: 4.8-5.2-5.2-4.16; Corresponding channels: 1, 2, 10, 20, 42
